quote.p:
In order to convenience German economy in relation to deliveries in
                                kind and to prevent any ill-effect from a too sudden cessation of
                                the 
 system in force it
                                is proposed that for a period of years that facility should remain
                                in existence on a diminishing scale as follows: 


                                        1929–30,
                                        600,000,000 gold marks;



                                        1930–31,
                                        550,000,000 gold marks;



                                        1931–32,
                                        500,000,000 gold marks;



                                        1932–33,
                                        450,000,000 gold marks;



                                        1933–34,
                                        400,000,000 gold marks;



                                        1934–35,
                                        350,000,000 gold marks;



                                        1935–36,
                                        300,000,000 gold marks.
